GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 2
SENATE BILL 124
House Committee Substitute Favorable 6/10/25
Short Title: State Hiring Accessibility and Modernization. (Public)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
February 24, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REDUCE BARRIERS TO STATE EMPLOYMENT AND TO MODERNIZE
3 THE STATE HUMAN RESOURCES SYSTEM.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5
6 REDUCE BARRIERS TO STATE EMPLOYMENT
7 SECTION 1. Article 2 of Chapter 126 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
8 a new section to read:
9 "§ 126-8.7. Reducing barriers to State employment.
10 (a) The State Human Resources Commission shall do all of the following:
11 (1) Regularly assess the educational, experiential, and training requirements
12 necessary for each position within each State agency, department, and
13 institution.
14 (2) Determine when practical experience and training, such as military service, an
15 apprenticeship, or a trade school education, rather than a four-year college
16 degree, is the appropriate qualification for a position.
17 (3) Identify jobs for which the educational, experiential, and training
18 requirements could be reduced from their present level.
19 (4) Remove language for a four-year college degree in position descriptions, to
20 the extent practicable, when they are not necessary for the position.
21 (b) Beginning October 1, 2025, and then annually thereafter, the State Human Resources
22 Commission shall report to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on General Government
23 on its efforts to reduce barriers to State employment as required by this section."
24
25 MAKE APPLYING FOR STATE JOBS EASIER
26 SECTION 2.(a) Article 5 of Chapter 126 of the General Statutes is amended by
27 adding a new section to read:
28 "§ 126-14.3A. Increasing efficiency of State job application process.
29 (a) The Office of State Human Resources (OSHR) shall streamline the job application
30 process for State positions by enabling applicants to upload resumes or website profiles. An
31 electronic tool shall be utilized to import information from these documents into the State job
32 application format, making the process more efficient while still collecting information necessary
33 for merit-based hiring under G.S. 126-14.2 and G.S. 126-14.3. An applicant remains responsible
34 for ensuring that all information required for initial screening appears correctly in the completed
35 State job application after importing the applicant's resume or profile.
