33 MAKE JOB POSTINGS EASIER TO UNDERSTAND AND EASIER FOR EMPLOYEES
34 TO QUALIFY
35 SECTION 3.(a) G.S. 126-14.2 reads as rewritten:
36 "§ 126-14.2. Political hirings limited.
37 …
38 (b) All State departments, agencies, and institutions shall select from the pool of the most
39 qualified persons for State government employment without regard to political affiliation or
40 political influence. For the purposes of this section, "qualified persons" shall mean each of the
41 State employees or applicants for initial State employment who:
42 (1) Have timely applied for a position in State government;
43 (2) Have the essential qualifications for that position; and
44 (3) Are determined to be substantially more qualified as compared to other
45 applicants for the position, after applying fair and valid job selection criteria,
46 in accordance with G.S. 126-5(e), G.S. 126-7.1, Articles 6 and 13 of this
47 Chapter, and State personnel policies approved by the State Human Resources
48 Commission.
49 For the purposes of this section, "essential qualifications" means the minimum education and
50 experience set forth in the class specification of the vacancy being filled. Any additional
51 qualifications, knowledge, skills, and abilities listed in the specific vacancy announcement shall
Page 2 Senate Bill 124-Second Edition

